umb="https://partner-upload-assets.wurl.com/peteski_productions_inc/DR_PHIL_L5123.jpg" title="Moms Gone Wild" userState="0" year="2007"><Image alt="Moms Gone Wild" type="background" url="https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/original/7L9GovbKdgyTW81Mi6DqW4rWuNW.jpg"/><Image alt="Moms Gone Wild" type="backgroundSquare" url="https://metadata-static.plex.tv/d/gracenote/decba2a31755ebf778b55eb3b6683782.jpg"/><Image alt="Moms Gone Wild" type="banner" url="https://artworks.thetvdb.com/banners/v4/series/408876/banners/611fb9f58d7c3.jpg"/><Image alt="Moms Gone Wild" type="coverArt" url="https://metadata-static.plex.tv/f/gracenote/fc65aa6053d82686a58d3277f1641dc9.jpg"/><Image alt="Moms Gone Wild" type="coverPoster" url="https://metadata-static.plex.tv/d/gracenote/d5ae43617cba5be7a6839347729abdad.jpg"/><Image alt="Moms Gone Wild" type="coverSquare" url="https://metadata-static.plex.tv/1/gracenote/1dcf05880c73aba916b31c1e8a646a25.jpg"/><Image alt="Moms Gone Wild" type="snapshot" url="https://partner-upload-assets.wurl.com/peteski_productions_inc/DR_PHIL_L5123.jpg"/><Genre filter="genre=6668f7413bfb7848eb535fff" id="6668f7413bfb7848eb535fff" key="/library/sections/home/all?genre=6668f7413bfb7848eb535fff" ratingKey="genre_6668f7413bfb7848eb535fff" slug="daytime-tv" tag="Daytime tv" type="directory" context="tag.genre"/><Media beginsAt="1778403399" duration="2814000" endsAt="1778406213" id="69f8914018b2cb4847e0b1d7" onAir="0" premiere="0" videoResolution="720" origin="livetv"/><Media beginsAt="1778430071" duration="2814000" endsAt="1778432885" id="69f8914018b2cb4847e0b1e0" onAir="0" premiere="0" videoResolution="720" origin="livetv"/></Video><Video guid="plex://episode/69f34b03c57a0d7c6a4b7ef1" key="/library/metadata/69f34b03c57a0d7c6a4b7ef1" ratingKey="69f34b03c57a0d7c6a4b7ef1" summary="After a Tennessee mother caused an international uproar when she sent her 7-year-old adopted son on a one-way flight back to Russia, the subject of international adoptions is making front-page headlines. Dr. Phil speaks with moms who say they relate to the Tennessee woman, and unless you walk a mile in their shoes, you have no way of understanding. Jane says she had no idea her 2-year-old daughter, Mikhaela, was profoundly deaf and autistic when she adopted her from the Ukraine eight years ago. Jane says the 10-year-old has multiple behavioral disorders and kicks, bites, punches and tries to hurt herself daily, and is getting too strong for her to handle. And, Kristi says all the love in the world couldn’t have helped the baby girl she adopted from China. Kristi says she wasn’t even close to being qualified to parent her now 14-year-old daughter, Tierney, who lives in a behavioral foster home in order to keep Kristi’s other children safe. If you’re thinking of adopting internationally, or if you’re an adoptive parent in crisis, don’t miss today’s show. Learn how to prepare for a cross-cultural adoption, how to get through the adoption process the correct way and what the experts have to say." type="episode" contentRating="TV-14" duration="2787000" grandparentArt="https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/original/7L9GovbKdgyTW81Mi6DqW4rWuNW.jpg" grandparentGuid="plex://show/611e2d860faece002cd7499d" grandparentKey="/library/metadata/66e4cbefd8c8d1be9ef71181" grandparentRatingKey="66e4cbefd8c8d1be9ef71181" grandparentThumb="https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/original/sPc9ncT29GSpuZTWAAm407FenyX.jpg" grandparentTitle="Dr. Phil" grandparentType="show" index="145" originallyAvailableAt="2010-06-02T00:00:00Z" parentIndex="8" requiresConsent="1" skipParent="1" thumb="https://partner-upload-assets.wurl.com/peteski_productions_inc/DR_PHIL_L8145.jpg" title="Adoption: Return to Sender?" userState="0" year="2010"><Image alt="Adoption: Return to Sender?" type="background" url="https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/original/7L9GovbKdgyTW81Mi6DqW4rWuNW.jpg"/><Image alt="Adoption: Return to Sender?" type="backgroundSquare" url="https://metadata-static.plex.tv/d/gracenote/decba2a31755ebf778b55eb3b6683782.jpg"/><Image